<br>
She pulled into the village with a large cart behind her horse, Zephyur.  She hopped down and looked around.  Deserted, as she had expected.  She only hoped everyone was staying warm and had plenty to eat.<br>
<br>
She brought on the cart 15 blankets;  4 deer skins made into capes;  two pairs of deer-skin boots, lined with fur;  twenty cords of firewood;  and 10 pounds of dried meat.::<br>
<br>
::She went to see her Queen, hoping for advice on how to distribute the supplies to those who need it the most.  She removed her leather gloves and knocked at Queen Hippolyte's door.  Her face was red - chapped from the searing wind she met with as she re-entered the village.  Her blonde hair hung about her face, as if trying to shield the cold.  She waited patiently, hoping she wasn't disturbing the always busy Queen.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/spinningsword.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 238<br> <font color=#993300>(2/13/01 1:56:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Supplies</span><hr size=1> :::As Hipp began to walk past her door to the altar room..she heard a knock.  Quickly her steps turned toward the door...where she lifted the heavy fur and skin layers that covered the entry way. She saw Nicodema and quickly waved her in:::: Hurry..get out of the cold, athelfi!  ::She smiled and moved so that Nicodema could enter.  She held the heavy layers that guarded the door..until Nicodema slipped thru the entrance.::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nicodemaalcinoe>Nicodema Alcinoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 10:53:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Supplies</span><hr size=1> ::Nods to the Queen::  Thank you.  I brought back supplies on a cart.  I was wondering, how can I distribute them?  I mean, who needs them the most.  I'll be more than happy to go back for more if you think we need them.  ::Smiles, moving from one foot to the other...a habit she picked up out in the cold::  I have some wonderful scrolls also.  Going out into the world was...well...an adventure.  ::Furrows her brow::  There are some very strange characters out there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/spinningsword.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#993300>(2/15/01 6:57:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> supplies</span><hr size=1> :::Hippolyte smiled listening to Nicodema::: I would love to hear of your travels, athelfi.  As for the supplies.  We have designated the hut next to the feast hall as the supply hut.  You can just take all the supplies that you brought to it.  Would you like some help? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nicodemaalcinoe>Nicodema Alcinoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#993300>(2/15/01 1:53:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Supplies</span><hr size=1> Umm...no, I think I can manage.  If there's anything else I can do for anyone...anything that will help, please let me know.  ::Nods and then straightens her furs, pulling her hood closer.  Pulls back the furs and steps back into the cold.  She makes sure to seal the entrance to the cave before leaving.::<br>
<br>
::Nico walks over to her horse and leads him to the hut next to the feast hall.  She begins unloading the cart, hoping that the meager supplies she brought will help her sisters during this terrible winter.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/spinningsword.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 244<br> <font color=#993300>(2/17/01 7:59:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> proud of an athelfi</span><hr size=1> :::Hippolyte smiled as Nicodema left.  She was so very thankful of the help that many of the athelfi poured into the village at this time.  The queen turned and walked to Hera's altar and began to light the candles.  As she did she whispered soft chants of thanks to the Queen of the Gods.  So, much had been given to the village in this time and since it's beginning.  Hippolyte would never forget the Goddess who had blessed them and her so much.::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nicodemaalcinoe>Nicodema Alcinoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#993300>(2/17/01 11:12:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ((Closing the topic))</span><hr size=1> ((Nicodema's scrolls of her journey to the outside villages will be posted on the &quot;Amazon Bardic Works&quot; boards.)) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersoft